OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1776258665
OL,3,CIrish government announces 505m euro
OL,4,Cin fuel-cost measures after protests
OL,6,FParticipants ` largely led by
OL,7,Fhauliers, farmers, and agricultural
OL,8,Fworkers ` began distinct but co-
OL,9,Fordinated action on Tuesday with slow-
OL,10,Fmoving convoys and outright stoppages
OL,11,Fon major motorways, as well as
OL,12,Fblockades of critical infrastructure
OL,13,Fwhich had largely wound down by midday
OL,14,Fon Sunday.
OL,16,FThe protesters had called on the Irish
OL,17,Fgovernment to take urgent action to
OL,18,Freduce fuel costs which they say are
OL,19,Fat unsustainable levels and will lead
OL,20,Fto people going out of business.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/4
